"COMBAT POSTURE"

Usage:  combat posture <posture>

The combat posture influences what kind of moves the player prefers in combat.
A player going all-out on their attack will not even attempt to defend
themselves; they will devote all their energy to offense, and get double the
normal number of attacks.  On the other hand, a player with an evasive posture
will not attempt an attack, but focus solely on avoiding harm to their person.

A normal posture focuses equally on offense and defense, so the postures may
be thought of in this context:

  DEFENSE  <-  evasive defensive normal offensive all-out  ->  OFFENSE

Choose your posture according to your character's style and circumstance.

See also:  COMBAT, COMBAT PROFILE, COMBAT SYSTEM, DAMAGE
