"COMBAT PROFILE"

The combat profile is a list of moves in combat that are automatically
performed by the player.  The moves may be offensive or defensive in nature;
they are executed as needed from the top down.  The combat profile may be
overridden by manual commands; manually performed moves will drain off speed
points from the profile, meaning that fewer, if any moves will then be
performed automatically.

For example, here's how the following profile will perform:

&cR1&cr)&cW  right swing&c0          Combat begins.  The player performs an offensive
&cR2&cr)&cY  right parry&c0          move; the profile starts at the top of the list, and
&cR3&cr)&cY  dodge&c0                finds an offensive move there.  The player swings 
&cR4&cr)&cW  left thrust&c0          whatever weapon they may have in their right hand.
&cR5&cr)&cL  none&c0
&cR6&cr)&cL  none&c0                 The foe gets their turn.  They successfully attack
&cR7&cr)&cL  none&c0                 and the player must defend.  The combat profile 
&cR8&cr)&cL  none&c0                 starts at the top looking for defenses, and finds one
                         in slot two.  The player attempts to parry with 
whatever weapon they may have in their right hand.  Another enemy jumps in,
and the player needs to defend again; this time they execute their third move,
and attempt to dodge aside.

The round ends, the next begins.  We'll say that the player, due to agility,
gets two attacks this round.  They left off with their right swing last round,
so the profile searches from that point and finds a left thrust in slot four.
The player swings whatever weapon they have there... oops!  No weapon!  They
wound up punching.

The player gets their second attack.  Searching down, the profile finds no
further moves, so it starts back up at the top.  It's another right swing.

We'll say that the player's foes are similarly charged, and the player faces
two swings from one and a thrust from the other.  The player will attempt a
right parry, dodge, and another right parry, in that order.

See also:  COMBAT, COMBAT POSTURE, COMBAT SYSTEM, DAMAGE
