DAMAGE

There are three basic types of damage:  basic, slashing, and piercing. They
differ in how much they harm the target, once armor is penetrated; slashing
damage does half again the normal damage, and piercing damage does double
because of the shock value.

This makes choice of weapons significant.  A mace and a dagger represent
opposite ends of the spectrum; a swing with a mace does large amounts of basic
damage, giving it greater chances to penetrate armor, while a thrust with a
dagger does less damage, but whatever damage gets through the armor is
doubled.

Choose axes, maces, and polearms, and similar when dealing with heavily
armored targets, and shortswords and daggers when dealing with light ones.  A
long sword represents an attractive middle point between these two opposites.

