"COLOR CODES"

You can change the color of your text inline in says, gossip, titles,
descriptions, and just about anywhere else with a simple color code.  The
codes are used as follows:

Type &^cX where X is a letter from the following table, as per the given
color:

   &cL&^cL  Dark Grey                      &cB&^cB  Blue
   &cR&^cR  Red                            &cM&^cM  Magenta
   &cG&^cG  Green                          &cC&^cC  Cyan
   &cY&^cY  Brown                          &cW&^cW  Light Grey

&c0To use boldface, simply capitalize the color letter, as in &^cC for
&cCBright Cyan.&c0  Background colors can be altered by using a &^bX
sequence.  And better yet:

   &^co  Foreground color off           &^b0  Background color off
   &cv&^cv  Reverse video  &c0                &cf&^cf  Flashing text&c0
   &^c0  All color off

The most common use for this, of course, is custom colors for communication.
A good example for this is the following command:  "alias ' '&^cG$*".

Finally, if you wish to echo a "&^c" to the screen, type "&^^c".
