SHEATH

Usage:  sheath [weapon] [scabbard]

Attempts to sheath a weapon in an appropriate empty scabbard.  If no weapon is
specified, the first weapon found in hand is assumed as the object.  The
equipment and inventory are then searched for the appropriate scabbard, wherein
