#0
SHOPS

Shops are places where the adventurer may purchase equipment for his quests,
and where he may sell his treasure if he should manage to survive the perils
with his life and sanity intact. Many shops trade only in a specific type of
merchandise. Thus, a baker may well refuse to buy your armor, even if it is of
high quality!
   To some people, the prospect of obtaining the entire inventory of a shop by
murdering the keeper may appear tempting - but beware: The shopkeepers are 
often rugged, capable men; roughened by years of trading and, indeed, surviving
in a world where the only safe prospect is death in the end.

See also: BUY, SELL, LIST, VALUE
#0
BUY
If you'd like to purchase an item from a shop and have the money, you can buy
it.  Items can be bought by name, or by their number in the shop listing,
and can be bought in quantity.
 
Examples:
 
> buy sword        (buy the first sword on the list)
> buy #3           (buy the third item on the list)
> buy 4.sword      (buy the fourth sword on the list)
> buy 10 bread     (buy 10 pieces of bread)
> buy 10 #2        (buy 10 of the second item on the list)
 
See also: SHOPS SELL LIST VALUE
#0
LIST

If you'd like to see what items a shop has for sale, take a look at the
list.  The list contains all of the items currently for sale and in
what quantity.  The price for each item is also listed.  If you are
interested in a particular type of item, you can specify which items to
list.
 
Examples:
 
> list             (list all items for sale)
> list sword       (list all swords for sale)
 
See also: SHOPS BUY SELL VALUE
#0
SELL

If you'd like to sell an item to a shopkeeper, trying selling it to them.
Most shops specialize in what they will buy, so you may have to look around
to find a buyer for your items.
 
Examples:
 
> sell sword       (sell the first sword in your inventory)
> sell 3 sword     (sell the first three swords in your inventory)
 
See also: SHOPS BUY LIST VALUE
#0
VALUE

Before selling an item to a shop, you can ask the shopkeeper how much
he or she is willing to pay for it.
 
Example:
 
> value bread
 
See also: SHOPS BUY SELL LIST
#0
ALCHEMIST ALCHEMISTS

Alchemists study the physical aspects of spells and gain their powers
through the combination of spell components. They are very secretive
about the components needed to cast their special spells and no scrolls
dealing with this are known to exist. It is known that every alchemist
spell requires at least three objects. When one component is in the 
alchemists inventory they will experience a certain physical effect, if
two, another effect, if all three, the magical powers of the alchemist and
his objects are released.

 Since the alchemist uses physical objects to cast their spells, they
require no mana, and are the most powerful of any type magics.

You can improve your skills by using the practice command.

See also: -
#0
ASSASSIN ASSASSINS

Assassins are the shadows that dance in the night. Sudden death is the
assassins moto. To this end they study the skills of dealing death in 
a quick effiecient manner. They are able to use any weapon and can
summon some very dangerous skills at higher levels. No one really ever
trusts an Assassin.

You can improve your skills by using the practice command.

See also: STRANGLE, HIDE, PUNCH, SNEAK
#0
CLERIC CLERICS

Clerics have an ancient belief in not carrying sharp weapons.  Hence, they can
only wield bludgeoning weapons.  This class gives you the wisdom of peace,
blessing and healing, though it is possible to learn more violent spells.

You can improve your spells by using the practice command.

See 'help spells' for a list of spells available.

See also: PRACTICE, SPELLS
#0
DWARF DWARVES

 The dwarven race is a stout robust lot who enjoy the caverns and caves 
beneath the dirt. They to, like the elves, are one of the oldest races, and
count theirs life spans in centuries. They tend to stay in their own groups
but are often seen traveling with humans and gnomes. From centuries of 
living underground dwarves have developed an acute sense of sight. They 
are able to see in the dark with infravison.
 
 Dwarves enjoy the following racial modifiers:
  
  + 1 Strength
  - 1 Wisdom
  + 1 Constitution
#0
ELF ELVES ELFS

 The elven race is a shy secretive group who tend to shun large groups not
of their race. Even though an elves life span is measured in centuries, 
they are a dieing race. Their inability to adapt well to a changing 
environment, and unwillingness to help others, in times of need, has served
them poorly. Elves have an acute sense of sight. They are able to see in
the dark with infravison.
 
 Elves enjoy the following racial modifiers:
  
  - 1 Strength
  + 1 Intelligence
  + 1 Wisdom
  - 1 Constitution
  + 1 Charisma
#0
RANGER RANGERS

Rangers are at peace with themselves and their knowlege of the woods. They
excell at hunting and tracking. They enjoy the strength of fighters, if not
the skills, yet retain their own special abilities. A Ranger is never
truly lost. The Ranger class has gained the limited use of some spells.

You can improve your skills and spells by using the practice command.

See also: TRACK, CAMOFLAGUE, PUNCH, HEADBUTT, SANCTUARY, CALL LIGHTNING,
          SKILLS, SECOUND ATTACK, THIRD ATTACK
#0
THIEF THIEVES

Thieves are known to have very special qualities, that no other class offers.
Their specialty tends to be in the darker, sneakier art.  Many of these
qualities can come in handy in many situations, such as picking locks.

You can improve you skills by using the practice command.

Skills available to thieves:

backstab, sneak, hide, steal, pick lock, punch.

See the help on each skill for more information.

See also: PRACTICE
#0
WARRIOR FIGHTER

Warriors are known to have more strength than the average player.  This makes
them better at hand-to-hand-combat, as they possess skills of violence and
fighting unequaled by the members of any other class.  However, they lack the
ability to use magic of any sort. Warriors also gain <with levels> the 
ability to attack more than once during a fight.

You can improve your skills by using the practice command.

Skills available to warriors:

rescue, bash, punch, headbutt, second attack, third attack.

See also: PRACTICE
#0
BACKSTAB

Backstab is a way to sneak up on a person and attempt to place your dagger
in his back, at exactly the point where it does most damage.  The chance and
success of a backstab are dependent upon the extent of your practice of the
skill at your guild.  You can always backstab sleeping people.

See also:  "skillinfo backstab", 
