PRACTICE PRACTISE

Usage: practice [skill or spell name]

Practice is the way you improve your spells and skills.  You can only do
so in your guild, where your guildmaster can help you train.  Type
"practice <skill>" to improve your abilities while in your guild.  You can
only practice a certain amount for each level you gain.  Unused practice
sessions will accumulate for use in future levels.

If you type practice anywhere other than in your guild, you will get a list
of all of the spells and skills you know and your level of proficiency at
each.

The practice screen displays skills in the format:

&cWSkill                        Base             Pts Mod  Proficiency
&cL-------------------------------------------------------------------
&cckick                         &cB[STR DEX       ]&cG   2  -1 &cy[&cm********&cb--&cy]&c0

This display, for example, shows that kick is rolled versus the average of the
character's strength and dexterity, that the character has invested two
practice sessions in the skill, that the skill roll has a modifier of -1
(actually an improvement over the default of -3), and finally, the overall
proficiency is rated by the bar graph.

When a guildmaster is in the room, the bar graph does not appear; instead,
your actual skill as it would be rolled on three six-sided dice and the cost
in gold of further improvement are displayed instead.

See also:  SKILLINFO, SPELLS
